{"type":"message","id":"1b96d12f","parentId":"71ce35ba","timestamp":"2026-03-26T01:12:27.338Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_78770db55f154ddc84f4990b","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.3.7 (42a1394) — I'm not AI-powered, I'm AI-possessed. Big difference.\n\nUsage: openclaw cron [options] [command]\n\nManage cron jobs (via Gateway)\n\nOptions:\n  -h, --help  Display help for command\n\nCommands:\n  add         Add a cron job\n  disable     Disable a cron job\n  edit        Edit a cron job (patch fields)\n  enable      Enable a cron job\n  help        Display help for command\n  list        List cron jobs\n  rm          Remove a cron job\n  run         Run a cron job now (debug)\n  runs        Show cron run history (JSONL-backed)\n  status      Show cron scheduler status\n\nDocs: https://docs.openclaw.ai/cli/cron"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":6019,"aggregated":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.3.7 (42a1394) — I'm not AI-powered, I'm AI-possessed. Big difference.\n\nUsage: openclaw cron [options] [command]\n\nManage cron jobs (via Gateway)\n\nOptions:\n  -h, --help  Display help for command\n\nCommands:\n  add         Add a cron job\n  disable     Disable a cron job\n  edit        Edit a cron job (patch fields)\n  enable      Enable a cron job\n  help        Display help for command\n  list        List cron jobs\n  rm          Remove a cron job\n  run         Run a cron job now (debug)\n  runs        Show cron run history (JSONL-backed)\n  status      Show cron scheduler status\n\nDocs: https://docs.openclaw.ai/cli/cron","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Administrator\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774487547336}}
{"type":"message","id":"2ff5686d","parentId":"1b96d12f","timestamp":"2026-03-26T01:12:30.022Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"完美！现在我可以使用 openclaw cron add 命令来添加定时任务。让我查看 add 命令的详细帮助。","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"完美！让我查看如何添加定时任务："},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_b0ec6451f796499ea2e5821f","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw cron add --help"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"zai","model":"glm-4.7","usage":{"input":178,"output":84,"cacheRead":57554,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":57816,"cost":{"input":0.0001068,"output":0.00018480000000000002,"cacheRead":0.00633094,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0066225400000000005}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774487547339}}
{"type":"message","id":"2665609a","parentId":"2ff5686d","timestamp":"2026-03-26T01:12:35.775Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_b0ec6451f796499ea2e5821f","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.3.7 (42a1394) — I've read more man pages than any human should—so you don't have to.\n\nUsage: openclaw cron add|create [options]\n\nAdd a cron job\n\nOptions:\n  --account <id>         Channel account id for delivery (multi-account setups)\n  --agent <id>           Agent id for this job\n  --announce             Announce summary to a chat (subagent-style) (default:\n                         false)\n  --at <when>            Run once at time (ISO) or +duration (e.g. 20m)\n  --best-effort-deliver  Do not fail the job if delivery fails (default: false)\n  --channel <channel>    Delivery channel (last) (default: \"last\")\n  --cron <expr>          Cron expression (5-field or 6-field with seconds)\n  --delete-after-run     Delete one-shot job after it succeeds (default: false)\n  --deliver              Deprecated (use --announce). Announces a summary to a\n                         chat.\n  --description <text>   Optional description\n  --disabled             Create job disabled (default: false)\n  --every <duration>     Run every duration (e.g. 10m, 1h)\n  --exact                Disable cron staggering (set stagger to 0) (default:\n                         false)\n  --expect-final         Wait for final response (agent) (default: false)\n  -h, --help             Display help for command\n  --json                 Output JSON (default: false)\n  --keep-after-run       Keep one-shot job after it succeeds (default: false)\n  --light-context        Use lightweight bootstrap context for agent jobs\n                         (default: false)\n  --message <text>       Agent message payload\n  --model <model>        Model override for agent jobs (provider/model or alias)\n  --name <name>          Job name\n  --no-deliver           Disable announce delivery and skip main-session summary\n  --session <target>     Session target (main|isolated)\n  --session-key <key>    Session key for job routing (e.g.\n                         agent:my-agent:my-session)\n  --stagger <duration>   Cron stagger window (e.g. 30s, 5m)\n  --system-event <text>  System event payload (main session)\n  --thinking <level>     Thinking level for agent jobs\n                         (off|minimal|low|medium|high)\n  --timeout <ms>         Timeout in ms (default: \"30000\")\n  --timeout-seconds <n>  Timeout seconds for agent jobs\n  --to <dest>            Delivery destination (E.164, Telegram chatId, or\n                         Discord channel/user)\n  --token <token>        Gateway token (if required)\n  --tz <iana>            Timezone for cron expressions (IANA) (default: \"\")\n  --url <url>            Gateway WebSocket URL (defaults to gateway.remote.url\n                         when configured)\n  --wake <mode>          Wake mode (now|next-heartbeat) (default: \"now\")"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":5750,"aggregated":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.3.7 (42a1394) — I've read more man pages than any human should—so you don't have to.\n\nUsage: openclaw cron add|create [options]\n\nAdd a cron job\n\nOptions:\n  --account <id>         Channel account id for delivery (multi-account setups)\n  --agent <id>           Agent id for this job\n  --announce             Announce summary to a chat (subagent-style) (default:\n                         false)\n  --at <when>            Run once at time (ISO) or +duration (e.g. 20m)\n  --best-effort-deliver  Do not fail the job if delivery fails (default: false)\n  --channel <channel>    Delivery channel (last) (default: \"last\")\n  --cron <expr>          Cron expression (5-field or 6-field with seconds)\n  --delete-after-run     Delete one-shot job after it succeeds (default: false)\n  --deliver              Deprecated (use --announce). Announces a summary to a\n                         chat.\n  --description <text>   Optional description\n  --disabled             Create job disabled (default: false)\n  --every <duration>     Run every duration (e.g. 10m, 1h)\n  --exact                Disable cron staggering (set stagger to 0) (default:\n                         false)\n  --expect-final         Wait for final response (agent) (default: false)\n  -h, --help             Display help for command\n  --json                 Output JSON (default: false)\n  --keep-after-run       Keep one-shot job after it succeeds (default: false)\n  --light-context        Use lightweight bootstrap context for agent jobs\n                         (default: false)\n  --message <text>       Agent message payload\n  --model <model>        Model override for agent jobs (provider/model or alias)\n  --name <name>          Job name\n  --no-deliver           Disable announce delivery and skip main-session summary\n  --session <target>     Session target (main|isolated)\n  --session-key <key>    Session key for job routing (e.g.\n                         agent:my-agent:my-session)\n  --stagger <duration>   Cron stagger window (e.g. 30s, 5m)\n  --system-event <text>  System event payload (main session)\n  --thinking <level>     Thinking level for agent jobs\n                         (off|minimal|low|medium|high)\n  --timeout <ms>         Timeout in ms (default: \"30000\")\n  --timeout-seconds <n>  Timeout seconds for agent jobs\n  --to <dest>            Delivery destination (E.164, Telegram chatId, or\n                         Discord channel/user)\n  --token <token>        Gateway token (if required)\n  --tz <iana>            Timezone for cron expressions (IANA) (default: \"\")\n  --url <url>            Gateway WebSocket URL (defaults to gateway.remote.url\n                         when configured)\n  --wake <mode>          Wake mode (now|next-heartbeat) (default: \"now\")","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Administrator\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774487555773}}
{"type":"message","id":"bfba1ca6","parentId":"2665609a","timestamp":"2026-03-26T01:12:46.221Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"好的，现在我知道如何使用 cron add 了。根据文档，我需要：\n1. 使用 --cron 指定 cron 表达式（工作日：0 10 * * 1-5 和 0 14 * * 1-5）\n2. 使用 --channel \"qqbot\"\n3. 使用 --to \"qqbot:c2c:DB0D276754D361B0256C70255C178BD8\"\n4. 使用 --message 指定发送的消息\n\n但是，我注意到 cron 命令是用来发送消息的，而不是运行 Python 脚本。我需要重新设计这个方案。\n\n实际上，我应该使用 --message 来发送一个消息给主会话，让它执行股票分析。或者，我可以使用 --system-event 来触发事件。\n\n让我重新思考：\n1. 方案A：使用 cron 直接发送消息给用户（但消息内容需要是股票分析结果）\n2. 方案B：使用 cron 发送消息到主会话，触发它运行股票分析\n\n我觉得方案B更合适。让我创建一个 cron 任务，在工作日10:00和14:00发送消息到当前会话，消息内容是\"分析股票\"。\n\n但是等等，这需要会话能够接收并处理这个消息。\n\n我注意到 payload 参数可以指定触发特定任务的参数，这给了我更多灵活性。我将尝试使用 --message 参数发送分析股票的指令，确保在工作日的指定时间点触发股票分析流程。通过精心设计 cron 表达式和消息内容，我可以实现自动化的股票分析通知。","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"完美！现在我来使用 OpenClaw 的 cron 功能创建定时任务 🚀"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_fce8f9f33a39485e91b9c1b5","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw cron add --name \"股票分析推送_10AM\" --cron \"0 10 * * 1-5\" --channel qqbot --to \"qqbot:c2c:DB0D276754D361B0256C70255C178BD8\" --message \"分析股票并推送结果\" --tz \"Asia/Shanghai\""}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"zai","model":"glm-4.7","usage":{"input":667,"output":757,"cacheRead":57786,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":59210,"cost":{"input":0.00040019999999999997,"output":0.0016654,"cacheRead":0.00635646,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00842206}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774487555776}}
